  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HCFC phase-out management plan (Stage II)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Stage I HPMP for Saint Lucia was approved at the 64th Meeting of the Executive Committee held in Montreal, 25 to 29 July 2011.  In principle, stage I of the HCFC phase-out management plan (HPMP) for Saint Lucia for the period 2011 to 2020 was approved at the funding level of US $232,207. Through the HPMP, the Government of Saint Lucia committed to phasing out 35 per cent of HCFC consumption by 2020, with an agreed estimated baseline of 0.92 ODP tonnes as its starting point for sustained aggregate reduction in HCFC consumption.  The second phase aiming to achieve 67.5% reduction in 2025 will be prepared and submitted in 2019.</narrative>
  </description>
